1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 7=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:36,070 --> 00:00:37,000
Pull me up.

4
00:00:37,030 --> 00:00:37,880
Hold on to it.

5
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:38,720
Slowly.

6
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,150
Listen, Chen.

7
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:54,280
You barely go out, getting rusty.

8
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,040
When it counts,

9
00:00:59,430 --> 00:01:00,600
I always have your back.

10
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:02,480
Come on.

11
00:01:10,870 --> 00:01:11,710
What's wrong?

12
00:01:12,230 --> 00:01:13,150
No idea.

13
00:01:13,310 --> 00:01:15,400
Something's pulling my leg down.

14
00:01:15,430 --> 00:01:16,350
Let me check.

15
00:01:17,310 --> 00:01:18,840
Snake! Snake!

16
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:19,680
It's still moving.

17
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:23,200
Not a snake. It's a vine.

18
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:24,780
- Rope!
- Rope!

19
00:01:24,780 --> 00:01:26,060
Anyone got a rope? Bring one.

20
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:31,403
- So generous.
- Thanks.

21
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,150
Ms. He, be careful.

22
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:37,430
There's no water or light,

23
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:38,400
but it's still alive.

24
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,870
It must've become a spirit.

25
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:41,070
Be careful.

26
00:01:41,350 --> 00:01:42,400
Peng, lend a hand.

27
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,840
Hurry up.

28
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:54,556
There's a plant called Welwitschia
in the desert.

29
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:55,950
It survives without water.

30
00:01:56,310 --> 00:01:57,280
It's not a big deal.

31
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,430
That's right.

32
00:02:01,150 --> 00:02:01,990
In my opinion,

33
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:05,280
we suddenly entered here

34
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:07,790
and changed something,

35
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,150
so it got active again.

36
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:11,870
Perhaps,

37
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,160
this is a welcome ceremony

38
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,430
they have for us.

39
00:03:06,630 --> 00:03:07,470
What's going on?

40
00:03:07,870 --> 00:03:08,800
It's moving!

41
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,240
Fire!

42
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:14,103
How did it come alive?

43
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,430
Shoot!

44
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:19,030
What is that thing? Fire!

45
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,520
Watch out!

46
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,260
How are these plants alive?

47
00:03:23,271 --> 00:03:24,530
They really turned into spirits.

48
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:25,680
What's going on?

49
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,030
We've got tree spirits here too.

50
00:03:28,430 --> 00:03:30,400
We're attacked from all sides.

51
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,190
- Hold tight!
- Hurry!

52
00:03:33,710 --> 00:03:34,870
Come on with me!

53
00:03:36,260 --> 00:03:37,120
Guard the right side!

54
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,470
Why are there so many tree trunks?

55
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,640
Too many!

56
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,400
There's more here!

57
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,630
Fire! Fire!

58
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:47,520
Why are there so many?

59
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,400
More on this side!

60
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:52,443
We can't finish them off!

61
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,840
Hurry up.

62
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:01,270
Chubby.

63
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,750
I'll count to three; then you let go.

64
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:06,036
We'll go through the tunnel;
let's meet ahead.

65
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,710
Alright, leave it to me.

66
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:08,550
Don't worry.

67
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:10,590
Hold on.

68
00:04:10,710 --> 00:04:11,550
One.

69
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:15,310
Two.

70
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:18,720
Three.

71
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,120
Chubby! Chubby!

72
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:21,360
Hurry, this way!

73
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:24,030
Watch out!

74
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,920
We can't finish them all!

75
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:30,256
They're getting more and more!

76
00:05:31,510 --> 00:05:32,480
Come on! Fall back!

77
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,393
Why are there so many?

78
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,160
This is unreal.

79
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,270
These things like light.

80
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,510
- Turn off the flashlights!
- I can't hold on!

81
00:05:45,510 --> 00:05:47,190
Turn off the flashlight.

82
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,360
Switch off the flashlight.

83
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,440
Kill the light.

84
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,190
- Hurry!
- Turn it off!

85
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:02,160
Lu, you actually guessed it right.

86
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,390
These things really love light.

87
00:06:04,830 --> 00:06:05,950
What the heck is that?

88
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,680
They're probably Man Catchers.

89
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:10,160
In Panama and on Java,

90
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,390
there are similar species.

91
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:13,456
They're super sensitive
to sound and light.

92
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:15,430
Kinda like a mimosa then?

93
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,390
What on earth is that thing?

94
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:18,720
Stay calm. Stay alert.

95
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:22,360
- Lu!
- Chubby!

96
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:23,750
Are you okay?

97
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,870
Chubby, where are you?

98
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,240
Up ahead, just keep walking.

99
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,720
I moved forward.

100
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,853
What are you reaching for?

101
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,160
Sorry, sorry.

102
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,680
It's a misunderstanding.

103
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:33,680
Lu, over here.

104
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,270
Right here.

105
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:36,270
I was so scared.

106
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,270
It's pitch black in here.

107
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,640
Don't you think

108
00:06:40,070 --> 00:06:41,830
this darkness feels kind of romantic?

109
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:44,070
Romantic, my foot.

110
00:06:45,390 --> 00:06:46,240
Where's the camera?

111
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:48,040
Give me the camera. Come on.

112
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,830
Here. Take it.

113
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:52,160
- Hold this for me.
- Which one?

114
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,600
Here, this one.

115
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,240
What are you doing?

116
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:01,920
This thing won't budge.

117
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,000
This scene

118
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,870
reminds me of the lights-out moment

119
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,480
at the weekend dance
in the cultural palace.

120
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:13,000
They always play
a romantic English song.

121
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,560
Sing a sad song.

122
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:18,510
It makes you stronger.

123
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,120
What's wrong with you? Stop it.

124
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,480
Why are you standing here?

125
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,040
What are you wearing?

126
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,880
Let me play with it.

127
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,360
Night vision goggles.

128
00:07:32,533 --> 00:07:33,720
You had this high-tech gadget?

129
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,360
Why didn't you take it out earlier?

130
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,800
Boss, there's a hole here.

131
00:07:42,310 --> 00:07:45,000
Miss Bai, let me light the way for you.

132
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:52,510
Chubby,

133
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,400
you go in first.

134
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:02,160
We've barely started.

135
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,510
You're scared already?

136
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,750
Cut the crap. Hurry up.

137
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:06,390
I'll show you how it's done.

138
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,720
Lu, the gear.

139
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:31,040
Even with this thing on, it's blinding.

140
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:33,720
This high-tech design
isn't scientific at all.

141
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,670
It should have levels

142
00:08:35,816 --> 00:08:36,840
for strong and weak light.

143
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,550
Get lost. You get in there too.

144
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:39,630
No, I...

145
00:08:39,630 --> 00:08:40,470
Hurry up.

146
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:41,630
This...

147
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,270
Can we walk through here?

148
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:49,840
Of course.

149
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,320
I'm not playing here.

150
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,750
If you don't want to die, follow me.

151
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,790
Don't play any tricks.

152
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:00,920
Do what you want.

153
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,320
I'm not begging you.

154
00:09:07,510 --> 00:09:08,480
Slow down.

155
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:30,960
Chubby,

156
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:33,240
this is the raider's tunnel?

157
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,080
That's right.

158
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,630
Are you sure?

159
00:09:35,790 --> 00:09:37,143
I don't even need to confirm that.

160
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,720
Isn't it obvious?

161
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:40,840
Right.

162
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,240
I forgot you're rookies.

163
00:09:42,910 --> 00:09:45,000
Come on, I'll educate you.

164
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,270
See this square tunnel?

165
00:09:47,510 --> 00:09:49,080
It's the Guanzhong-style tunnel.

166
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:51,870
Masterpiece of northern tomb raiders.

167
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,320
Look at this craftsmanship.

168
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,390
As Lu would say,

169
00:09:55,390 --> 00:09:56,616
it's already polished with age.

170
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,960
Feel that texture.

171
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,120
I'm not a fool.

172
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:03,960
Chubby,

173
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:06,510
that was really a close call just now.

174
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,120
That tree branch spirit.

175
00:10:08,390 --> 00:10:10,120
What the hell was that thing?

176
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,550
I honestly don't know.

177
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,960
But it's no good
since it was trying to wrap us.

178
00:10:26,670 --> 00:10:28,240
Stop digging the dirt.

179
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,910
What exactly was this tunnel used for?

180
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:54,910
I originally thought

181
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:56,840
it was dug by that Ridge Mover.

182
00:10:57,720 --> 00:11:00,150
But the walls and ground
are smooth and flat.

183
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,840
It looks like it was dug in advance.

184
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,960
That is strange.

185
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:06,510
There's no way back.

186
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:08,120
Let's move forward.

187
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:14,589
I wonder how Chubby
and the others are doing.

188
00:11:14,870 --> 00:11:16,216
It's not his first time in a tomb.

189
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,530
Nothing will happen to him.

190
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,790
He'll be fine.

191
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,720
But he's not alone.

192
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:24,440
Bai Lingling?

193
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:26,240
Exactly.

194
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,750
Have you ever seen a tomb raider

195
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,390
bring that many mercenaries?

196
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:32,630
They also have many weapons.

197
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,113
Who knows
where she transported them from?

198
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,750
She's just a tomb raider.

199
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,030
She invited us to enter the tomb.

200
00:11:39,543 --> 00:11:41,816
She won't do anything to us
before she reaches her goal.

201
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:46,150
But have you ever thought about it?

202
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,870
She's so young and pretty.

203
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,873
Why would she do this for a living?

204
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:52,000
Thinking about that now is useless.

205
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:54,810
Let's find a way to meet up
with them first.

206
00:11:55,390 --> 00:11:56,960
We'll deal with the rest later.

207
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,080
Is she pretty?

208
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,150
I think she's alright.

209
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:06,120
Just average.

210
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:07,470
Assemble!

211
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:10,790
Dress right.

212
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,390
Eyes front.

213
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:14,673
Comrades.

214
00:12:14,684 --> 00:12:15,972
(Police)
This tomb-raiding gang

215
00:12:15,983 --> 00:12:17,270
is carrying guns and ammunition.

216
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:18,430
They are extremely dangerous.

217
00:12:18,790 --> 00:12:20,810
During the operation,
you must ensure your safety.

218
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,509
We must not let them leave
Xuanyi County.

219
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:23,240
Understood?

220
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,080
Understood.

221
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,110
Move out.

222
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,160
Lu!

223
00:12:28,930 --> 00:12:29,790
Wait.

224
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,320
I didn't mean to.

225
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:33,120
Don't you like digging dirt?

226
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:35,080
Then we'll just cut off your fingers.

227
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,120
No, no, no.

228
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:42,960
Let me go.

229
00:12:43,050 --> 00:12:43,910
Huang Long,

230
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,480
come at me if you dare!

231
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,750
Why beat him?

232
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:48,390
Stop.

233
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:51,840
What place is this?

234
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:52,980
Talk.

235
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,960
How would I know where this is?

236
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,750
If I knew, I wouldn't have come.

237
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:58,270
I regret it so much.

238
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:03,320
This big face. Smooth facial surface.

239
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:06,150
The ears are proportionally large.

240
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,630
No obvious gender features.

241
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:12,870
This should be
a Western Zhou bronze piece.

242
00:13:14,670 --> 00:13:15,790
You can tell it's bronze

243
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:17,550
just by looking?

244
00:13:17,550 --> 00:13:18,960
What if it's plaster?

245
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:20,705
As for what it's made of,

246
00:13:20,716 --> 00:13:21,870
we'll know after one shot.

247
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,120
Use your words.

248
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,840
Why resort to violence?

249
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:35,390
If we chisel this down,

250
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:38,150
do you know how much it'd fetch
at Sotheby's?

251
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:41,240
You're so generous,
smashing it just like that.

252
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,080
Why not smash everything here?

253
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:46,510
Not firing recklessly is my rule.

254
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:48,080
Do your work

255
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:50,440
or get out right now.

256
00:13:51,270 --> 00:13:52,480
Everyone.

257
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,870
Let me say something, alright?

258
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,093
Do you know what this is?

259
00:13:55,550 --> 00:13:56,870
They're from Western Zhou.

260
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:59,840
Everything here is a treasure.

261
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:02,480
One shot can cost several cars.

262
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:04,360
Are you sure they're from Western Zhou?

263
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:07,150
I'm an expert in this.

264
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:10,030
Look at the patterns on the wall.

265
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:12,550
This bronze piece is the real deal.

266
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:13,910
Look at that patina.

267
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,030
Everything matches.

268
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:18,920
Bro,

269
00:14:19,390 --> 00:14:22,030
even if you sell it for money,

270
00:14:22,030 --> 00:14:22,910
I won't stop you.

271
00:14:23,266 --> 00:14:24,360
But please don't destroy it.

272
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,720
That would disgrace the ancestors.

273
00:14:26,550 --> 00:14:27,910
You seem to know quite a lot.

274
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:28,750
Of course.

275
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:30,790
Do you know who Lu is?

276
00:14:32,330 --> 00:14:33,180
Lu is

277
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,630
an expert in cultural relics.

278
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:39,120
When restoring ancient swords
and musical instruments,

279
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,550
Lu must be present.

280
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,910
Being able to meet Lu

281
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:45,840
means you're extremely lucky.

282
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:47,360
No, no. Just a small business.

283
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,840
Fine. We know they're antiques now.

284
00:14:50,670 --> 00:14:51,510
So, what now?

285
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:52,990
Shall we dig it down?

286
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:56,069
These are all narrow passages.

287
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:58,120
If you dig it down,
how will you transport it out?

288
00:14:58,240 --> 00:14:59,270
Take it apart.

289
